      • convertHashMapToStringArray

        public static java.lang.String[] convertHashMapToStringArray(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> inputMap)
        Converts a Hash map from strings to integers into an array of Strings in such a way that: if(HashMap("s") = i THEN out[i] = s, where out denotes the output array. Precondition: all strings are mapped to unique integers within the range of (0,size of the input hashMap)
        Parameters:
        inputMap - input hash map that maps strings to integers
        Returns:
        an array of strings corresponding to the inputMap
